<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,836,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Affinities.</emphasis>
This species is unique among the known female 
<emphasis box="[876,999,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName box="[876,995,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Perlomyia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
by having two large, bean-shaped and well-separated median sclerites on sternum VIII. Slightly similar median sclerites occur on 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivec &amp; Stark, 2012" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Perlomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honshu">
<emphasis box="[1219,1331,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">P. honshu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2012 a) Seven new species of Perlomyia (Plecoptera: Leuctridae) from Japan. Illiesia, 8 (7), 94 - 103." type="journal article" year="2012" yearSuffix="a">
Sivec &amp; Stark, 
<number box="[223,282,908,932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" value="2012.0">2012</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but those are much smaller, and laterally surrounded by additional dark sclerites.
</paragraph>
